OL,3,CMore than half of students at Guernsey
OL,4,Cschool speak an additional language
OL,6,F"I think it's so important that our
OL,7,Fschool reflects the world that we live
OL,8,Fin nowadays. We have children from all
OL,9,Faround the world. It has such a
OL,10,Fwonderful inclusive feel here and I
OL,11,Fthink our children have so much
OL,12,Frespect for each other. That's a vital
OL,13,Fskill as they move out into the world."
OL,15,FAround 10% of Guernsey schoolchildren,
OL,16,Fapproximately 669 students, do not
OL,17,Fspeak English as their first language.
